{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c27a775a-a7e5-4c2b-b2b1-63ee1a9bd4d8","content":"Here are the **evaluation performance issues** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. File I/O Property Function (High Impact)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nReading files via property functions executes during **every evaluation pass** (IntelliSense, design-time builds, restore, etc.). This is expensive and blocks the evaluation thread synchronously.\n\n**Fix:** Move file reading to a target with `Inputs/Outputs` so it only runs during execution, not evaluation.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Overly Broad Glob (Medium Impact)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nA recursive `**\\*.*` glob walks the entire directory tree at evaluation time. As the repo grows (or if `node_modules`/`.git`/artifacts are present), this becomes increasingly slow.\n\n**Fix:** Add large directories to `DefaultItemExcludes` or narrow the glob to specific extensions/paths.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deep Import Chain (Low-Medium Impact)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nA 3-level chain here is modest, but this pattern scales poorly. Each import adds an evaluation phase pass. In production repos this often grows to 20+ levels, compounding cost.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Issue | Severity | Remedy |\n|-------|----------|--------|\n| `File::ReadAllText` in property | 🔴 High | Move to a build target |\n| `**\\*.*` recursive glob | 🟡 Medium | Narrow scope or exclude dirs |\n| Nested import chain | 🟢 Low | Keep flat where possible |\n\nThe highest-priority fix is removing the `System.IO.File` call from evaluation—it runs on every IDE keystroke and every `dotnet` invocation.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fb32b19f-8483-47f5-8b34-498da0831855","outputTokens":469,"requestId":"7C11:38FB84:146ACF3:16E127A:6A027FC1"},"id":"da6ecb4e-9980-4295-b4a7-2f0e1723f7e6","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:18:06.856Z","parentId":"31395e1f-1df6-48a0-a9d9-b8f89a3844d3"}
